<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="540" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,655,680]" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to Project 
<taxonomicName box="[782,870,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zadbi">
<collectionCode box="[782,870,656,680]" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">ZADBI</collectionCode>
</taxonomicName>
, the Zurquí All 
<taxonomicName authority="Biodiversity Inventory." authorityName="Biodiversity Inventory." box="[1073,1437,655,680]" kingdom="Plantae" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" rank="order">Diptera Biodiversity Inventory.</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[151,352,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zadbi">
<emphasis box="[151,352,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">Mesoconius zadbi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and most of the other 
<taxonomicName box="[604,738,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[604,738,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">Mesoconius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species newly described here are described partly on the basis of specimens from Project 
<taxonomicName box="[453,542,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zadbi">
<collectionCode box="[453,542,728,752]" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">ZADBI</collectionCode>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="540" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,764,789]" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">Comments.</emphasis>
Although this species remains known only from males, 
<taxonomicName box="[982,1081,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zadbi">
<emphasis box="[982,1081,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">M. zadbi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly belongs in 
<taxonomicName box="[1302,1436,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1302,1436,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">Mesoconius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be placed in a clade characterized by a paired spermathecal duct with a striate basal half and a smooth distal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">
This species is similar to the South American 
<taxonomicName box="[737,967,872,896]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infestus">
<emphasis box="[737,967,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">Mesoconius infestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but differs most obviously by its black mid and hind femora with contrasting orange apices. 
<taxonomicName box="[816,914,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zadbi">
<emphasis box="[816,914,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">M. zadbi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably most closely related to 
<emphasis box="[1314,1436,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="540">
<taxonomicName box="[1314,1432,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">M. bicolor</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but characters of the as yet unknown males are needed to test that hypothesis.
</paragraph>
